[SN]TITLE[SN]
Connor Ballantyne admits rape of four-year-old girl in Moray

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A teenager has admitted sex crimes against two children, including the rape of a four-year-old girl, in Moray.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Connor Ballantyne, 18, pleaded guilty to raping the child in Dufftown between December 2011 and October 2012.
He also admitted sexual offences involving a 10-year-old boy in Elgin between November and December 2012.
Ballantyne, of Elgin, admitted the offences at the High Court in Edinburgh. Judge Lord Stewart deferred sentence to a hearing on 9 July.
